    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-29T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="70"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.61331/113: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the First
                        Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Salisbury</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-29T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 29, 1938—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>270. Your 589, September 28, 4 p.m.,<note n="73" xml:id="d70fn73">Not
                        printed.</note> Universal Leaf Tobacco Company. You are authorized, in
                    accordance with the request of the company, to make an approach to the Japanese
                    Embassy in Peiping along the lines of the Department’s 332, September 22, 8
                    p.m., to Tokyo, provided you and the Ambassador feel that such an approach might
                    serve some useful purpose.</p>
                <p>Inform Tokyo and Tsingtao of any action taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
